In C++, most of the features from the Standard Library (like cout, cin, vector, string, etc.) are kept inside a container called a namespace — specifically, the std namespace.(we write std::cout,std::endl if we not use using namespace std)
Writing using namespace std; tells the compiler: "Bhai, ab se agar koi standard library ka feature use ho, toh mujhe baar-baar std:: likhne ki zarurat na pade."
  
concept------=>  <iostream> ek header file hai jo input-output ke tools provide karti hai — jaise:
cin → user se input lena
cout → screen pe output dena

concept------=> #include ka main kaam hota hai:
✅ Header file ko tumhare code ke saath jodna, taaki us headerfile ke andar likhe hue tools, functions, aur classes tum use kar sako.
  ex=#include <vector>                                                                    
Isse tum vector naam ka data type use kar sakte ho.
Vector is like a dynamic array — matlab size badhta-ghatta sakta hai runtime pe.
Example:
cpp
#include <vector>
vector<int> nums;
nums.push_back(10);

ex=2.#include <string>
Isse tum string data type use kar sakte ho.
Built-in C++ ka class hai jo text data store karta hai.
Example:
cpp
#include <string>
string name = "Shubhanshu";

NOTE---->> #include<bits/stdc++.h> includes all the libraries whatever libraries are in c++.so hume #include<iostream><#include<vector> ye sab likhna nahi 
Compile karna = Code ko Machine Language mein badalna

concept------->
🧮 Compile Time – Jab Code Ban Raha Hota Hai
Ye woh waqt hota hai jab:

Tumhara C++ code compiler ke through process ho raha hota hai.

Errors like syntax mistakes (galat spelling, missing semicolon, etc.) yahin detect hote hain.

Code ko machine language mein convert kiya jaata hai (binary format).

🛠️ Example Error:
cpp
int x
cout << x;

– Missing semicolon → Compile time error

concept------>
  Run Time – Jab Code Chal Raha Hota Hai
Ye woh waqt hota hai jab:

Tumhara program execute ho raha hota hai.

User input liya jaa raha hai, loops chal rahe hain, output aa raha hai.

Yahan logical errors ya unexpected conditions detect hote hain — like divide by zero or invalid input.

💥 Example Run-time error:

cpp
int a = 5, b = 0;
cout << a / b; // Division by zero → Run time crash

concept----.Library =Aisa code jo pehle se kisi ne likh diya hai, aur tum usse directly apne program mein use kar sakte ho — bina khud dobara likhne ki mehnat kiye
Example:
Tumhe sorting karni hai → C++ mein sort() function already library mein hota hai.

Tum bas #include <algorithm> likh ke wo function use kar sakte ho.

🧪 Real-life example:
Socho library ek toolbox hai 🧰 Tum bolte ho:

"Mujhe screwdriver chahiye." Toh tum toolbox khol ke screwdriver nikaal lete ho — bina banaye direct use

Standard Libraries (built-in C++)
Library Name	Purpose	ExampleUse
<iostream>	Input/output	cin, cout
<vector>	Dynamic array (STL container)	vector<int> v;
<string>	Text handling	string name = "Shubhanshu";
<algorithm>	Common algorithms	sort(v.begin(), v.end());
<cmath>	Math functions	sqrt(x), pow(x, y)
<map>	Key-value data structure	map<string, int> m;
